Federal Reserve Bank of Dallas 
President  Richard Fisher  talks about the  U.S. economy  and Fed 
monetary policy.  Fisher, speaking on Bloomberg Radio's "The Hays Advantage,"
said he is seeing "minor momentum" in the U.S. economy, and the 
central bank has "plenty of ammunition" left if the economic 
situation turns "horrific." (Source: Bloomberg)  00:00 Prospects for stagflation
